Stein Mart, Inc. (NASDAQ:SMRT) Sees Significantly Lower Trading Volume - Highlight Press























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Stein Mart, Inc. (NASDAQ:SMRT) Sees Significantly Lower Trading Volume
July 17, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





(NASDAQ:SMRT) shares saw light trading volume with 1,031K shares changing hands on Friday.  Volume was down 53.46% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here is the rundown on market activity for Stein Mart, Inc. (NASDAQ:SMRT).   Director Mitchell W. Legler acquired 45,000 shares at a price of $1.53 on Wed the 24th. That brings the Director’s holdings to $457,635 as reported to the SEC. Chairman Jay Stein purchased 900,000 shares at a price of $1.51 on Wed the 24th. The Chairman now owns $3,727,927 of the stock as recorded in a recent Form 4 SEC filing.
 Richard L. Sisisky, Director bought $75,500 worth of shares at an average price of $1.51 on May 23rd. That brings Sisisky’s holdings to $204,380 per an SEC filing yesterday.
 These firms have also modified their investment in SMRT.   Creative Planning augmented its investment by buying 4,000 shares an increase of 181.8% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Creative Planning controls 6,200 shares valued at $10,000. The value of the position overall is up by 42.9%. Morgan Stanley reduced its stake by selling 750 shares a decrease of 4.7%. Morgan Stanley now holds 15,348 shares worth $46,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 47.7%.
 As of quarter end Goldman Sachs Group Inc had acquired  a total of 6,104 shares growing its stake by 54.2%. The value of the investment in SMRT went from $62,000 to $52,000 a change of 16.1% for the reporting period. As of the end of the quarter Hightower Advisors, LLC had bought 27,367 shares growing its holdings by 87.8%. The value of the total investment in Stein Mart, Inc. increased from $170,000 to $179,000 increasing 5.3% since the last quarter.





  On September 30, 2016 the stock rating was set at “Neutral” in a report from Johnson Rice which was a cut from the previous “” rating. On September 29 the company was changed to a “Neutral” according to a Sidoti & Co. report which is down from the previous “Buy” rating.
 On May 9 the stock rating was downgraded to “Neutral” from “” in a report from Northland Securities. On February 13, 2014 Canaccord Genuity starting coverage on SMRT by announcing an initial rating of “Buy” and price target of $18.00.
 February 5 investment analysts at Sidoti & Co. held the price target at $16.00 but upgraded the company from Neutral to Buy. On February 5 the company was upgraded from “Neutral” to “Buy” with a current price target of $16.00 by analysts at Sidoti & Co..
 In the market the company is trading down from yesterday’s close of $1.2.  Shares are trading at $1.16 barely below $1.59, the 50 day moving average and which is slightly below the 200 day moving average of $3.05.  The 50 day moving average was down by -27.65% and the 200 day average moved down $-1.90. 
 In the latest earnings report the EPS was $-0.20 and is estimated to be $-0.09 for the current year with 47,621,000 shares now outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS to be $-0.20 with next year’s EPS projected to be $0.15. 
 Stein Mart, Inc., launched on October 14, 1983, is a national retailer offering the fashion merchandise, service and presentation of a department or specialty store. The Company offers apparel for women and men, as well as accessories, shoes and home fashions. The Business’s target customers are women over 45 years old. The Company operates approximately 280 stores in over 30 states and an Internet store. Its stores are located in the Northeast, Midwest, Southeast, Texas and the Southwest. It is concentrated in the Southeast and Texas where over 180 of its stores are located..






